</td></tr><tr><td class="article-table">ok, ok.  i know:  it's been forever since the last update.  i blame everyone but myself.  let me indulge you by trying to actually remember (which isn't so easy for me these days, mind you) just what sorta things we've been up to:<br />
<br />
(editor's note:  please remember that dunze is a moron when it comes to HTML so you'll be seeing no nifty screenshots or pictures here today, although i'm sure dunze will make good use of flowery imagery in order to paint a mental picture for you, the reader, so much that you'll almost feel as if you were there fighting and dying and killing alongside the mighty cultists yourself.)<br />
<br />
ahem.  anyway, we finally got around to trying the burrower encounter in the deep and, i've got to say, everything that everyone has said about this being an actually well-balanced ring encounter is true.  it was challenging and fun without requiring the 80-person force that most other rings seem to call for.  in the end, the burrower parasite died in what i think was an 82 minute fight (although the first 60 minutes were spent trying to find his melee hitbox).  he dropped 2 different rings, a rogue dagger and his range orb thingie.  everyone was happy and nindail sang a song.<br />
<br />
we've fought the AoW a couple times since our last update.  the first attempt we killed him, but the second try the other day we weren't so fortunate.  as a side note to that, i'd like to mention to Feigns, level 48 iksar monk, that if we ever see you near one of our raids again there's gonna be hell to pay (that is, unless you've already been banned for the stunt you pulled -- or for having such a *cool ass name* as a monk.  feigns.  monk.  feign death.  get it?  hahahah so cool.  wow.  and ya know, it's kinda disconcerting when you talk to a gm and give them a name and their response is, &quot;oh dear.  not him again.&quot;).  but anyway, i digress.....<br />
<br />
tunare popped.  we cleared the plane.  we killed the goddess.  not much else to say about that.<br />
<br />
we've also been killing greig pretty regularly, but mostly because tattle loves the fight so very, very much.  last night we put down the thought horror fiend, too, and then promptly regretted having spent the time clearing to him once loot was called.  oh well, c'est la vie.  a special thanks to the aetherium and wraith people at the zone for helping me spam-inspect tattle into linkdeath after he fell asleep during our crawl.<br />
<br />
let's see, what else.  oh yeah, we blew the shei spawn!  grats us.  it was our first attempt at the guy, so we didn't really know what to expect, although we learned a lot and i'm sure we'll fare much better when we next face him (or her -- i can never tell).  while we were there we also killed the itraer vius, maybe more than once actually, i'm not really sure.<br />
<br />
we put down lendi the keeper and zlandicar recently, too, for old time's sake.  funny to think back on the trouble those mobs gave us when velious first came out.  we also killed the new and improved sontalak a couple times and i'd like to go on the record as saying i think that a mob that procs an AE is just plain stupid. but that's just me.<br />
<br />
we also had our run in north tov this past week.  it was a bit of a sloppy run, but i'm just going to mark it down to being out of practice since it's been about 4 weeks since our last go.  we came.  we cleared.  we got loot. nothing rotted.  the end.<br />
<br />
so i *think* that's about it.  i'll try to update the site much more regularly, although i just accepted a position designing quests for the new My Little Pony (tm) MMORPG so my time is going to become a scarce commodity soon.  worry not, dear readers, there will be no key camping quests to raid the high end stable dungeons as long as i have a say in it!<br />
<br />
lastly, i know how much you people love the stalker quotes, so i'll do my best to recreate some here for you (remember, no pictures):<br />
